snippet: With the Yankees holding a 5-3 lead in the fourth, Joba Chamberlain came in and struck out four in an inning and two-thirds and earned the victory.
abstract: New York Yankees relief pitcher Joba Chamberlain earns his first victory of the year, striking out four batters in team's 13-3 victory over Baltimore Orioles.
lead_paragraph: With the Yankees holding a 5-3 lead in the fourth, Joba Chamberlain came in and struck out four in an inning and two-thirds and earned the victory.

headline.seo: Yankees’ Chamberlain Is Sharp With Game on the Line
headline.main: Girardi Shows His Faith; Chamberlain Shows His Stuff
